<TITLE> DSE opens upbeat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 11 (bdnews24.com)- Dhaka stocks opened upbeat Monday after closing lower the previous day. Share prices of most issues continued to rise till midday due to investors' buying spree. Dhaka Stock Exchange's general index started to fall in the opening hour of trading. It however gained significantly on the second hour and remained more or less stable till the midday sessions to remain higher from the previous day. The benchmark DGEN or general index at 12.42 pm rose 8.26 points or 0.27 percent to 2983.64 while the DSI or all share price index was at 2508.55, up by 6.20 points or 0.24 percent. Turnover stood at Tk 1.17 billion from 90,75407 traded shares with 110 issues gaining, 91 losing and some 18 holding steady. At 12.44 pm, AB Bank topped the turnover board, trading higher at Tk 2900 from Sunday's Tk 2870.75. Grameen Mutual Fund One however fell to Tk 120.20 from Tk 121.10. State-run oil entity Meghna Petroleum also slumped to Tk 343.60 from previous day's closing of Tk 348.40. Power sector bigwig, Summit Power rose to Tk 1603 from Tk 1600.50. IDLC attracted investors' attention on Monday. It surged to Tk 1785 from Tk 1643.25. Among the other scrips on the turnover board IFIC and BRAC Bank also gained. Jamuna Oil, AIMS 1st mutual Fund and NBL however fell. b
